{"sha": "1a1e427caae53ffa42d0f192b3d75045e3637539", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0MTM2NTMxMDA6MWExZTQyN2NhYWU1M2ZmYTQyZDBmMTkyYjNkNzUwNDVlMzYzNzUzOQ==", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "jwakely@redhat.com", "date": "2019-05-10T21:41:23Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "redi@gcc.gnu.org", "date": "2019-05-10T21:41:23Z"}, "message": "PR libstdc++/81266 fix std::thread::native_handle_type test\n\nThe test uses remove_pointer because in most cases native_handle_type is\na pointer to the actual type that the C++ class contains. However, for\nstd::thread, native_handle_type is the same type as the type contained\nin std::thread, and so remove_pointer is not needed. On targets where\npthread_t is a pointer type remove_pointer<native_handle_type> is not a\nno-op, instead it transforms pthread_t and causes the test to fail.\n\nThe fix is to not apply remove_pointer when testing std::thread.\n\n\tPR libstdc++/81266\n\t* testsuite/util/thread/all.h: Do not use remove_pointer for\n\tstd::thread::native_handle_type.\n\nFrom-SVN: r271080", "tree": {"sha": "203e529f73adb76020a5f469cde0cff29dbb7be4", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/203e529f73adb76020a5f469cde0cff29dbb7be4"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/1a1e427caae53ffa42d0f192b3d75045e3637539", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/1a1e427caae53ffa42d0f192b3d75045e3637539", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/1a1e427caae53ffa42d0f192b3d75045e3637539", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/1a1e427caae53ffa42d0f192b3d75045e3637539/comments", "author": {"login": "jwakely", "id": 1254480, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyNTQ0ODA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1254480?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/j